media-process-staging - Media Staging Processor

USAGE:
    media-process-staging

DESCRIPTION:
    Process media files from staging area and move to organized
    directory structure. Handles permissions, git annex operations,
    and creates ZFS snapshots.

PROCESS:
    1. Remove spaces from filenames
    2. Move files to output/raw by-time directories
    3. Set correct ownership
    4. Git annex add and commit
    5. Create ZFS snapshot
    6. Cleanup empty staging directories

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-media-mountpoint PATH
        Media mountpoint directory

    -conf-media-user USER
        Media file owner

    -conf-media-volume VOLUME
        ZFS volume name

    -conf-media-retention PERIOD
        Snapshot retention period

NOTE:
    Requires root privileges.

EXAMPLES:
    media-process-staging
